      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SKY KEEPING (7) ran seventh in a Grade 4/5 last time, copping a check in the run and finishing 16 lengths from the winner over 400m at this track. Has two wins from Box 7. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Well worth another try. DOTTIE KEEPING (5) was a little disappointing last start at Grafton when 5th (20.00) over 350m. Has won here at this journey. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. ELSA ABOVE (4) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, half a length from the winner Cheryl Blue (24.70) at Gunnedah. Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Will give a great sight again. HYBRID EVE (8) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
